Readonly observableFunction

observableFunction: string | ((DataFrame: any, any: any) => Serie<IArray>)

Inherited from SkinConfiguration.observableFunction

  • Defined in src/lib/models.ts:68

The observableFunction is a function that map a line of a [[KeplerMesh.Dataframe]] to the quantity of interest to observe.

Each line of the dataframe correspond to some properties available for a particular vertex. The dimension of the quantity to observe depends on the skin used: for most of them it is a scalar (e.g. for ModuleIsoContours), but there can be cases (e.g. streamlines) where a 3D vector is expected.
